# Copy to `.env` in the repo root and fill in. Start the API with: npm run build && npm start
#
# These are your *OAuth application* credentials (one per Patreon app). They are NOT
# the creator’s access/refresh tokens — those are obtained only after a user completes
# OAuth and are stored encrypted (see web/.env.example + /patreon/connect flow).

# Required: Patreon OAuth app (Client ID / Client Secret from developer portal).
PATREON_CLIENT_ID=
PATREON_CLIENT_SECRET=

# Required: 32-byte key, base64 — used to encrypt stored Patreon access/refresh tokens.
# Example: node -e "console.log(require('crypto').randomBytes(32).toString('base64'))"
RELAY_TOKEN_ENCRYPTION_KEY=

# Optional: override token endpoint (default: https://www.patreon.com/api/oauth2/token)
# PATREON_TOKEN_URL=

# Optional: sync watermark storage (default: .relay-data/patreon_sync_watermarks.json)
# RELAY_PATREON_SYNC_WATERMARK_PATH=

# API listen port (default 8787 — matches web/lib/relay-api.ts default)
# PORT=8787

# --- Not used as env vars in this codebase ---
# "Client API Version" (e.g. v2): choose in the Patreon portal only; pass ?api_version=2
# on Patreon resource requests when you implement the Patreon fetch/sync layer.
#
# "Creator's Access Token" / "Creator's Refresh Token" from the portal: do not paste
# into .env. After OAuth, this app stores encrypted tokens via POST /api/v1/auth/patreon/exchange
# in RELAY_CREDENTIAL_STORE_PATH (default .relay-data/patreon_credentials.json).
#
# How to test OAuth end-to-end:
# 1. Register redirect http://localhost:3000/patreon/callback (or your chosen URL) in Patreon.
# 2. Root .env: PATREON_CLIENT_ID, PATREON_CLIENT_SECRET, RELAY_TOKEN_ENCRYPTION_KEY → npm run build && npm start
# 3. web/.env.local: NEXT_PUBLIC_* from web/.env.example → cd web && npm run dev
# 4. Open http://localhost:3000/patreon/connect → Continue to Patreon → approve → callback exchanges code.
# 5. Pull posts into Relay: POST /api/v1/patreon/scrape with { "creator_id": "...", "dry_run": true } first.
# Automated test (no real Patreon): npm test — tests/workstream-a.patreon-oauth.happy-path.test.ts mocks the token URL.
